label.value: host comorbidity datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the quality of the host to have a comorbidity.

label.value: host pathogen exposure datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that  records the presence of a prior infection or immune memory to a pathogen.

label.value: challenge-killing interval datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that  records the interval between the vaccine challenge and the sacrifice of the organism during a vaccine challenge.

label.value: challenge admistration route datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the route of a pathogen challenge occurs in.

label.value: sacrifice process datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the method of sacrifice (i.e. killing).

label.value: host adverse event  to vaccine datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the presence or abasence of adverse event in a host in response of some vaccine.

label.value: assay mesurement datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the measurement of an assay.

label.value: assay  measurement sample  interval

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the time point between the start of a first intervention in a planned process and the measurment of a sample.

label.value: assay type datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the type of assay used.

label.value: assay analysis tool version datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the version of an analysis tool (software) used for an assay.

label.value: assay platform datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the type of platform used for an assay.

label.value: pathogen attenuation datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the utilization of an attenaution process on a pathogen.

label.value: vaccination frequency datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the number of occurences the host was vaccinated as part of the vaccination process.

label.value: vaccination interval datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the interval between vaccinations of a host.

label.value: vaccine target datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the intended target of a vaccine.

label.value: vaccine vector datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the vaccine vector of a vaccine.

label.value: vaccine preservative datum

definition.value: A measurment datum that records the vaccine preservative of a vaccine.

label.value: vaccine challenge survival assay

definition.value: An assay that measures the survival rate of organisms exposed to a pathogen.

label.value: pathogen gut adhesion assay

definition.value: An assay that measures the gut adhesion of a pathogen within an organism.

label.value: viral neutralization titer assay

definition.value: An assay that measures the titer of antibodies that neturalize a pathogen within an organism.

label.value: study design variable

definition.value: A directive information entity that is part of a study design. It can be eithor independent variables whose values are selected to determine its relationship to an observed phenomenon (the dependent variable) or dependent variables that are studied and expected to change when the independent variable varies.
